.TH "BREW\-CASK\-EXTRACT" "1" "April 2026" "Homebrew"
.SH NAME
brew\-cask\-extract \- Extract a cask from Homebrew\'s git history into a personal tap
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBbrew\fP \fBcask\-extract\fP [\fIoptions\fP] \fIcask\fP \fItap\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Extract a cask from Homebrew\[u2019]s git history into a personal tap\. Optionally add a postflight block to remove macOS\[u2019]s quarantine extended attribute so un\-notarized apps can launch without Gatekeeper blocking them\.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display any debugging information\.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Make some output more quiet\.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Make some output more verbose\.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show this message\.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fP
Extract the cask at this specific version from git history\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-quarantine\fP
Add a \fBpostflight\fP block that removes the quarantine xattr\.
.TP
\fB\-\-unversioned\fP
Copy without adding a version suffix to the cask token\.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fP
Overwrite the destination file if it already exists\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-shard\fP
Write to a flat \fBCasks/\fP directory instead of a sharded one\.
